==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Obstacle
<hw>Ob"sta*cle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>obstaculum</ets>, fr. <ets>obstare</ets> to withstand, oppose;
<ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) + <ets>stare</ets> to stand. See
<er>Stand</er>. and cf. <er>Oust</er>, <pos>v.</pos>]</ety> <def>That
which stands in the way, or opposes; anything that hinders progress; a
hindrance; an obstruction, physical or moral.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If all <qex>obstacles</qex> were cut away.⟦br⟧
And that my path were even to the crown.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Impediment; obstuction; hindrance; difficulty.
See <er>Impediment</er>, and <er>Obstruction</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obstancy</ent>⟦br⟧
